00:00:04.113 --> 00:00:08.051 position:5% line:77% align:start
[GIRL] You wanna walk to a place
that's different than this one,
don't you?

00:00:08.051 --> 00:00:10.253 position:24% line:83% align:start
To the warm place
full of secrets?

00:00:10.253 --> 00:00:12.355 position:24% line:83% align:start
To the world where
every day is fun?

00:00:12.355 --> 00:00:15.192 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's what you've wanted
all along, isn't it?

00:00:15.192 --> 00:00:16.795 position:33% line:89% align:start
Okay, then.

00:00:16.795 --> 00:00:19.899 position:19% line:89% align:start
Let's go... together.

00:00:19.899 --> 00:00:22.168 position:16% line:89% align:start
@ <i>[music playing]</i>

00:01:50.349 --> 00:01:51.785 position:5% line:89% align:start
[small boy laughing obnoxiously]

00:01:51.785 --> 00:01:54.121 position:7% line:89% align:start
[BOY] Hey, Mommy, look. Look!

00:01:54.121 --> 00:01:56.857 position:16% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER] Hang on a sec.
[BOY] Come on, Mommy!

00:01:56.857 --> 00:01:58.994 position:30% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] Hey...

00:01:58.994 --> 00:01:59.995 position:33% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:02.098 position:30% line:89% align:start
Play with me.

00:02:02.098 --> 00:02:04.935 position:16% line:83% align:start
All right, well, what do
you do with Sanae?

00:02:04.935 --> 00:02:06.237 position:21% line:89% align:start
She reads me books.

00:02:06.237 --> 00:02:08.640 position:24% line:83% align:start
Did you bring any
books with you?

00:02:10.441 --> 00:02:11.911 position:10% line:89% align:start
What about with the old man?

00:02:11.911 --> 00:02:13.012 position:35% line:89% align:start
Baseball.

00:02:13.012 --> 00:02:15.248 position:24% line:89% align:start
You play baseball?

00:02:15.248 --> 00:02:17.051 position:24% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] Like this.

00:02:20.255 --> 00:02:21.622 position:13% line:89% align:start
[in a deep voice] Komada!

00:02:21.622 --> 00:02:24.127 position:10% line:89% align:start
Are you doing an impression?

00:02:24.127 --> 00:02:25.360 position:13% line:89% align:start
You mean, it isn't funny?

00:02:25.360 --> 00:02:28.032 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's not funny at all.

00:02:28.032 --> 00:02:30.235 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's too bad.

00:02:30.235 --> 00:02:32.737 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>What the heck is he</i>
 <i>teaching her?</i>

00:02:34.639 --> 00:02:38.578 position:16% line:83% align:start
[BOY loudly] Mommy! Hey!
Mommy, listen to me!

00:02:38.578 --> 00:02:41.115 position:7% line:83% align:start
[MOTHER] Shh, okay? Sit down.
[BOY] I don't wanna!

00:02:41.115 --> 00:02:44.786 position:13% line:77% align:start
[MOTHER] Be quiet! You're
causing a scene. [BOY] Come on,
Mommy, now!

00:02:44.786 --> 00:02:45.955 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOY]
But you're not listening, Mommy!

00:02:45.955 --> 00:02:47.290 position:38% line:89% align:start
SHUT UP!

00:02:47.290 --> 00:02:50.093 position:13% line:83% align:start
There are other people on
this train, you know!

00:02:50.093 --> 00:02:51.728 position:16% line:89% align:start
Sorry... [BOY] Mommy...

00:02:51.728 --> 00:02:54.432 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'll keep him quiet.

00:02:54.432 --> 00:02:56.400 position:35% line:89% align:start
Dammit...

00:03:00.106 --> 00:03:01.908 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ushio?

00:03:03.310 --> 00:03:05.579 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA]
Where the heck did she go?

00:03:08.617 --> 00:03:10.486 position:30% line:89% align:start
Gimme a break.

00:03:10.486 --> 00:03:14.524 position:10% line:77% align:start
Ushio, let me know first if
you're going to the bathroom,
okay?

00:03:15.659 --> 00:03:17.795 position:19% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] What's wrong?

00:03:19.430 --> 00:03:21.967 position:7% line:89% align:start
You weren't crying, were you?

00:03:23.336 --> 00:03:26.140 position:16% line:89% align:start
C'mon, don't lie to me.

00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:27.241 position:5% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] I'm not supposed to cry.

00:03:27.241 --> 00:03:29.410 position:16% line:89% align:start
Huh? Who told you that?

00:03:29.410 --> 00:03:30.779 position:30% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] Sanae.

00:03:30.779 --> 00:03:31.914 position:41% line:89% align:start
Sanae?

00:03:31.914 --> 00:03:34.416 position:10% line:83% align:start
Even she can be strict, huh?
Who knew?

00:03:34.416 --> 00:03:37.888 position:5% line:83% align:start
[USHIO] But she said there's one
place where it's okay to cry.

00:03:38.656 --> 00:03:40.759 position:24% line:89% align:start
And where is that?

00:03:43.963 --> 00:03:45.898 position:27% line:89% align:start
In the bathroom.

00:03:45.898 --> 00:03:51.339 position:10% line:77% align:start
Fair enough. I guess nobody
would see you crying if you did
it in the bathroom.

00:03:51.339 --> 00:03:55.277 position:7% line:77% align:start
But if you feel like crying, I
don't think you should have to
hold back.

00:03:55.277 --> 00:03:58.281 position:16% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA] You should cry
while you still can.

00:03:58.281 --> 00:04:01.085 position:21% line:83% align:start
When you get bigger,
sometimes you can't cry.

00:04:01.085 --> 00:04:03.956 position:13% line:83% align:start
Even if you have something
you want to cry about...

00:04:18.274 --> 00:04:19.642 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hey.

00:04:19.642 --> 00:04:21.878 position:13% line:89% align:start
Want me to buy you a toy?

00:04:21.878 --> 00:04:24.415 position:5% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA] Pick whatever you want.
It's on me.

00:04:24.415 --> 00:04:26.217 position:30% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] Okay.

00:04:33.093 --> 00:04:34.661 position:30% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] Hey.

00:04:34.661 --> 00:04:37.064 position:27% line:83% align:start
Maybe you'd like
this one instead?

00:04:43.272 --> 00:04:45.575 position:5% line:89% align:start
It's fine if you don't like it.

00:04:45.575 --> 00:04:49.214 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, I mean, you'd probably
rather have a girl's toy, right?

00:04:49.214 --> 00:04:50.849 position:19% line:89% align:start
Instead of a robot...

00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:53.452 position:19% line:89% align:start
Girl toys are boring.

00:04:53.452 --> 00:04:55.088 position:30% line:89% align:start
I like robots.

00:04:55.088 --> 00:04:58.792 position:7% line:83% align:start
Well, there's no harm I guess.
It's just a little strange.

00:04:58.792 --> 00:05:01.195 position:7% line:89% align:start
No, never mind. Keep playing.

00:05:03.465 --> 00:05:06.635 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>I wonder if she's enjoying</i>
 <i>her summer vacation.</i>

00:05:06.635 --> 00:05:10.875 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Probably not, since she's</i>
 <i>stuck with a guy like me.</i>

00:05:18.918 --> 00:05:20.621 position:19% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] What's wrong?

00:05:20.621 --> 00:05:22.623 position:33% line:89% align:start
Gotta potty.

00:05:22.623 --> 00:05:25.026 position:33% line:89% align:start
Number two.

00:05:25.026 --> 00:05:27.196 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA]
It's dark, so be careful.

00:05:27.196 --> 00:05:28.998 position:41% line:89% align:start
'Kay.

00:05:37.342 --> 00:05:38.777 position:5% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] I did it all by myself.

00:05:38.777 --> 00:05:40.780 position:30% line:89% align:start
Good for you.

00:05:43.650 --> 00:05:44.852 position:13% line:89% align:start
So, what is it this time?

00:05:44.852 --> 00:05:47.355 position:21% line:89% align:start
What is that thing?

00:05:47.355 --> 00:05:51.060 position:21% line:83% align:start
Oh, it's a firefly.
You know what that is, right?

00:05:51.060 --> 00:05:52.962 position:10% line:89% align:start
I've never seen one before.

00:05:52.962 --> 00:05:55.666 position:7% line:89% align:start
They must come out later here.

00:06:01.107 --> 00:06:03.276 position:27% line:89% align:start
Something wrong?

00:06:03.276 --> 00:06:06.414 position:7% line:83% align:start
What, do you I have something
funny on my face?

00:06:06.414 --> 00:06:09.951 position:10% line:83% align:start
Then stop staring at me like
that. It's not very polite.

00:06:12.221 --> 00:06:13.622 position:16% line:89% align:start
C'mon, what do you want?

00:06:13.622 --> 00:06:17.528 position:7% line:83% align:start
If there's something you wanna
say, then just say it.

00:06:17.528 --> 00:06:22.367 position:5% line:77% align:start
I get it. You won't talk 'cause
you're still afraid of me,
aren't you?

00:06:22.367 --> 00:06:24.069 position:5% line:89% align:start
All right, out with it already.

00:06:24.069 --> 00:06:27.274 position:24% line:83% align:start
I promise I won't
yell anymore, okay?

00:06:29.376 --> 00:06:32.714 position:19% line:83% align:start
I want you to tell me
about my mommy.

00:06:34.316 --> 00:06:35.718 position:16% line:89% align:start
Why don't you ask Sanae?

00:06:35.718 --> 00:06:38.021 position:16% line:83% align:start
I did, but she wouldn't
say anything to me.

00:06:38.021 --> 00:06:40.891 position:13% line:89% align:start
Wants me to tell you, huh?

00:06:41.926 --> 00:06:43.529 position:10% line:89% align:start
Ask Sanae when we get back.

00:06:43.529 --> 00:06:46.398 position:10% line:83% align:start
Say that you asked me and I
wouldn't tell you anything.

00:07:08.126 --> 00:07:11.997 position:7% line:89% align:start
Ushio, don't fall asleep now.

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:16.470 position:7% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA] Here! Gotta put your
hat on the right way.

00:07:16.470 --> 00:07:19.841 position:5% line:83% align:start
Hope you're ready to go, we got
a whole lot of walking to do.

00:07:22.612 --> 00:07:25.014 position:16% line:89% align:start
Let's go. [USHIO] Okay.

00:07:40.935 --> 00:07:43.004 position:27% line:89% align:start
This is amazing.

00:07:44.540 --> 00:07:46.108 position:5% line:89% align:start
Do you wanna have a better view?

00:07:46.108 --> 00:07:48.411 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh! [TOMOYA] 'Kay.

00:07:48.411 --> 00:07:50.815 position:19% line:83% align:start
Here, spread your feet
apart for me.

00:07:54.687 --> 00:07:56.489 position:13% line:89% align:start
Wow, you're really light.

00:07:56.489 --> 00:07:58.291 position:41% line:89% align:start
Look!

00:08:00.928 --> 00:08:02.564 position:35% line:89% align:start
How is it?

00:08:02.564 --> 00:08:05.967 position:10% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] Wow! It's so pretty!

00:08:11.508 --> 00:08:15.079 position:13% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA] Don't go too far.
Stay where I can see you!

00:08:15.079 --> 00:08:18.517 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>I guess taking this trip was</i>
 <i>worth it after all. [Ushio</i>
 <i>laughing and playing]</i>

00:08:35.306 --> 00:08:37.542 position:30% line:89% align:start
What's wrong?

00:08:37.542 --> 00:08:39.144 position:24% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] It's gone.

00:08:39.978 --> 00:08:42.481 position:24% line:89% align:start
What do you mean?

00:08:42.481 --> 00:08:44.418 position:30% line:89% align:start
I lost my toy.

00:08:46.721 --> 00:08:48.456 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's not over here.

00:08:48.456 --> 00:08:52.561 position:5% line:83% align:start
You sure you didn't accidentally
run off and play somewhere else?

00:08:52.561 --> 00:08:54.331 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, if you were only
playing over here,

00:08:54.331 --> 00:08:57.033 position:5% line:83% align:start
then it seems like we should've
found the thing already.

00:08:58.034 --> 00:09:00.271 position:24% line:83% align:start
Ushio, let's just
forget about it.

00:09:00.271 --> 00:09:04.142 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'll buy another one just like
it on the way home, okay?

00:09:04.142 --> 00:09:05.911 position:21% line:89% align:start
But I want that one.

00:09:05.911 --> 00:09:08.515 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's gone now.
There's nothing we can do.

00:09:10.417 --> 00:09:13.088 position:24% line:83% align:start
Who taught you to
be so stubborn?

00:09:36.718 --> 00:09:38.887 position:27% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] Ushio!

00:09:38.887 --> 00:09:41.157 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna go further down the
way for a little bit, all right?

00:09:41.157 --> 00:09:42.659 position:16% line:89% align:start
Just stay there for now.

00:09:42.659 --> 00:09:44.461 position:30% line:89% align:start
[USHIO] Okay.

00:09:52.037 --> 00:09:53.440 position:10% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] <i>What is this?</i>

00:09:53.440 --> 00:09:55.942 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>It feels like I've</i>
 <i>been here before.</i>

00:10:10.328 --> 00:10:13.265 position:7% line:83% align:start
[WOMAN] You're Tomoya Okazaki,
aren't you?

00:10:15.669 --> 00:10:17.304 position:16% line:89% align:start
[TOMOYA] Uh, yes, ma'am.

00:10:17.304 --> 00:10:20.140 position:35% line:83% align:start
But, uh...
Have we met somewhere before?

00:10:20.140 --> 00:10:23.044 position:13% line:83% align:start
[WOMAN] Yes, although you
were quite young.

00:10:23.044 --> 00:10:25.715 position:13% line:89% align:start
My name is Shino Okazaki.

00:10:26.483 --> 00:10:27.918 position:38% line:89% align:start
Okazaki?

00:10:27.918 --> 00:10:30.053 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm your grandmother, Tomoya.

00:10:30.053 --> 00:10:33.191 position:13% line:89% align:start
Naoyuki Okazaki is my son.

00:10:36.563 --> 00:10:40.568 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SHINO] I was contacted by
someone named Furukawa.

00:10:40.568 --> 00:10:44.873 position:16% line:77% align:start
She said that you would
eventually come if I waited
here.

00:10:44.873 --> 00:10:46.776 position:38% line:83% align:start
[TOMOYA]
So, Sanae planned this...

00:10:46.776 --> 00:10:49.445 position:21% line:83% align:start
You've grown so much
since I last saw you.

00:10:49.445 --> 00:10:52.216 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry,
I don't remember at all.

00:10:53.585 --> 00:10:56.689 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, I can hardly blame you
since you were so young.

00:10:56.689 --> 00:10:58.524 position:13% line:83% align:start
We met right on this spot,
actually,

00:10:58.524 --> 00:11:02.061 position:13% line:83% align:start
shortly after your mother
Atsuko passed away.

00:11:04.197 --> 00:11:06.667 position:5% line:83% align:start
I haven't spoken to your father
in quite a while.

00:11:06.667 --> 00:11:09.238 position:24% line:83% align:start
Is he still paying
for his crime?

00:11:09.238 --> 00:11:11.073 position:19% line:83% align:start
No, he's been released
from prison.

00:11:11.073 --> 00:11:13.142 position:5% line:89% align:start
He's back home as far as I know.

00:11:13.142 --> 00:11:16.547 position:30% line:83% align:start
Such a shame;
It must have been hard on you.

00:11:16.547 --> 00:11:18.215 position:33% line:89% align:start
Not really.

00:11:20.218 --> 00:11:24.725 position:7% line:77% align:start
He may have been brash when he
was younger, but he certainly
wasn't THAT foolish.

00:11:24.725 --> 00:11:28.429 position:5% line:77% align:start
Both Atsuko and your father were
still in high school when they
got engaged,

00:11:28.429 --> 00:11:31.332 position:30% line:83% align:start
so of course,
we were against the marriage.

00:11:31.332 --> 00:11:33.937 position:7% line:83% align:start
After the wedding, your father
dropped out of school.

00:11:33.937 --> 00:11:38.275 position:10% line:77% align:start
He could only afford a tiny
apartment, but they wanted to
live on their own.

00:11:38.275 --> 00:11:42.548 position:16% line:83% align:start
Still, they both seemed
so happy back then.

00:11:42.548 --> 00:11:46.286 position:10% line:83% align:start
After all, he was caring for
the woman he loved.

00:11:46.286 --> 00:11:50.224 position:19% line:83% align:start
It was probably all he
ever wanted in life.

00:11:50.224 --> 00:11:55.363 position:7% line:77% align:start
It wasn't too long after that
when Atsuko became pregnant with
you.

00:11:55.363 --> 00:11:57.800 position:24% line:83% align:start
You were certainly
a blessing to them.

00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.270 position:5% line:89% align:start
They were thrilled to have you.

00:12:04.809 --> 00:12:10.215 position:7% line:83% align:start
Unfortunately, all good things
must come to an end, I suppose.

00:12:10.215 --> 00:12:15.857 position:7% line:77% align:start
It wasn't long after you were
born that Atsuko passed away in
an accident.

00:12:15.857 --> 00:12:17.960 position:5% line:89% align:start
It was so crushing for Naoyuki.

00:12:17.960 --> 00:12:21.331 position:10% line:77% align:start
At first, I thought he would
never recover from his
depression.

00:12:21.331 --> 00:12:23.099 position:24% line:89% align:start
But he was strong.

00:12:23.099 --> 00:12:28.173 position:5% line:83% align:start
He held on to what hope he could
muster and kept pushing on.

00:12:35.215 --> 00:12:37.952 position:27% line:89% align:start
Do you know why?

00:12:37.952 --> 00:12:42.792 position:10% line:77% align:start
He couldn't give up on life,
because he was left with you,
Tomoya.

00:12:42.792 --> 00:12:45.863 position:21% line:83% align:start
He was determined to
raise you on his own.

00:12:48.032 --> 00:12:49.901 position:27% line:89% align:start
It was long ago,

00:12:49.901 --> 00:12:53.205 position:5% line:83% align:start
but I'll never forget that day,
when he walked away from here,

00:12:53.205 --> 00:12:55.508 position:7% line:89% align:start
holding your hand and smiling.

00:12:55.508 --> 00:12:58.345 position:13% line:89% align:start
Perhaps you remember now?

00:12:58.345 --> 00:13:00.982 position:16% line:83% align:start
The days after that were
the toughest in his life.

00:13:00.982 --> 00:13:04.520 position:16% line:83% align:start
I can't even imagine how
hard he had to work.

00:13:04.520 --> 00:13:06.923 position:19% line:83% align:start
He was fired from one
job after another

00:13:06.923 --> 00:13:11.562 position:5% line:77% align:start
and forced to move from place to
place just to keep his head
above water.

00:13:11.562 --> 00:13:16.136 position:16% line:83% align:start
Still, he always did his
best to care for you.

00:13:16.136 --> 00:13:20.407 position:10% line:77% align:start
He would try to cheer you up
with toys or sweets whenever he
could spare a little money.

00:13:20.407 --> 00:13:25.614 position:10% line:77% align:start
He sacrificed everything for
you, but he refused to leave you
behind.

00:13:25.614 --> 00:13:29.485 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm sure he was strict,
perhaps even violent at times,

00:13:29.485 --> 00:13:33.691 position:10% line:77% align:start
but in his heart, I know the
only thing he wanted was to
raise you well,

00:13:33.691 --> 00:13:37.629 position:13% line:83% align:start
even if you were too young
to understand that.

00:13:37.629 --> 00:13:41.500 position:5% line:83% align:start
But it was a very hard life for
him, and nobody's perfect.

00:13:41.500 --> 00:13:45.940 position:13% line:77% align:start
I know he often turned to
alcohol to forget his troubles
at work.

00:13:45.940 --> 00:13:50.012 position:5% line:77% align:start
I'm sure that must've been hard
for you, dealing with an
alcoholic father.

00:13:50.012 --> 00:13:53.950 position:16% line:77% align:start
And I'm sure he did some
terrible things when he was
drunk.

00:13:53.950 --> 00:13:58.589 position:5% line:77% align:start
But please keep in mind that he
chose to live this life with
you,

00:13:58.589 --> 00:14:01.259 position:19% line:83% align:start
no matter how painful
it was for him.

00:14:01.259 --> 00:14:02.962 position:21% line:89% align:start
And so you grew up.

00:14:02.962 --> 00:14:04.764 position:19% line:83% align:start
Before long, you were
a fine young man

00:14:04.764 --> 00:14:07.401 position:13% line:83% align:start
who was old enough to make
decisions about his own life.

00:14:07.401 --> 00:14:10.705 position:16% line:83% align:start
But by then, Naoyuki had
already lost everything.

00:14:10.705 --> 00:14:13.409 position:10% line:83% align:start
His career, his reputation,
his friends,

00:14:13.409 --> 00:14:17.114 position:7% line:83% align:start
and even the love of his son,
I'm sure.

00:14:17.114 --> 00:14:21.786 position:10% line:77% align:start
Furukawa told me that you're
suffering in the same way that
Naoyuki was back then.

00:14:21.786 --> 00:14:24.123 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm truly sorry to hear that.

00:14:24.123 --> 00:14:26.192 position:10% line:83% align:start
You know, that's the reason
I came here today.

00:14:26.192 --> 00:14:29.295 position:10% line:83% align:start
